Package: woodcoind
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 Woodcoin is a free open source peer-to-peer electronic cash system that
 is completely decentralized, without the need for a central server or
 trusted parties.  Users hold the crypto keys to their own money and
 transact directly with each other, with the help of a P2P network to
 check for double-spending.
 .
 Woodcoin differs from Bitcoin primarily in its distribution and signature
 methods.
 .
 This package provides woodcoind, a combined daemon and CLI tool to
 interact with the daemon.

Package: woodcoin-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 Woodcoin is a free open source peer-to-peer electronic cash system that
 is completely decentralized, without the need for a central server or
 trusted parties.  Users hold the crypto keys to their own money and
 transact directly with each other, with the help of a P2P network to
 check for double-spending.
 .
 Woodcoin differs from Bitcoin primarily in its distribution and signature
 methods.
 .
 This package provides Woodcoin-Qt, a GUI for Woodcoin based on Qt.
